question:
In the five-sided star shown, the letters $A$, $B$, $C$, $D$, and $E$ are replaced by the numbers 41, 43, 44, 45, and 47, although not necessarily in this order. The sums of the numbers at the ends of the line segments $\overline{AB}$, $\overline{BC}$, $\overline{CD}$, $\overline{DE}$, and $\overline{EA}$ form an arithmetic sequence, although not necessarily in this order.  What is the middle term of the arithmetic sequence?

[asy]
pair A,B,C,D,E;
A=(0,10);
B=(5.9,-8.1);
C=(-9.5,3.1);
D=(9.5,3.1);
E=(-5.9,-8.1);
draw(A--B--C--D--E--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
label("$A$",A,N);
label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$C$",C,NW);
label("$D$",D,NE);
label("$E$",E,SW);
[/asy]

