&=\left(\frac{1}{2}\sqrt{5.7\times 10^{8}}\right)^2+(312768)^2\\
&=\frac{2.85\times 10^{8}}{4}+9.76\times 10^{8}\\
&=2.36\times 10^{8}+9.76\times 10^{8}\\
&=1.12\times 10^{9}
\end{align*}

So the distance from the center point $P$ of one square base to the corner $Q$ of the opposite base is $\sqrt{1.12\times 10^{9}}$ cm, which is equal to $\boxed{105600}$ cm.

